1 AN ACT
2 To enact R.S. 47:1703.4, relative to ad valorem tax exemptions; to extend eligibility for ad
3 valorem tax exemptions for certain manufacturing activities and facilities; to provide
4 for definitions; to provide for an effective date; and to provide for related matters.
5 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
6 Section 1. R.S. 47:1703.4 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
7 §1703.4. Exemption; aerospace manufacturing activities
8 A. The legislature finds that certain advanced manufacturing activities
9 associated with aerospace programs are critical to economic development and shall
10 be eligible for the ad valorem tax exemption pursuant to Article VII, Section 21(F)
11 of the Constitution of Louisiana.
12 B. For the purposes of this Section, the following terms shall have the
13 following meanings:
14 (1) "Aerospace manufacturing" means the fabrication, assembly, integration,
15 testing, preparation, and launch of vehicles and craft as part of aerospace activities.
16 (2) "Aerospace manufacturing establishment" means any facility used in
17 aerospace activities, including but not limited to pads, structures, propellant systems,
18 testing infrastructure, and related support systems that are functionally integrated
19 with the manufacturing process.
20 C. Aerospace manufacturing and capital expenditures related to facilities and
21 infrastructure integral to aerospace manufacturing shall be eligible for the ad valorem
22 tax exemption pursuant to Article VII, Section 21(F) of the Constitution of
23 Louisiana.
